   Enroll eligible land in USDA conservation programs: Conservation
   Reserve Program (CRP), Wetlands Reserve Program (WRP), Wildlife Habitat
   Incentives Program (WHIP) and Conservation Reserve Enhancement Program
   (CREP) offer long term rental payments, incentive payments, and
   cost-share payments for converting eligible farmland to buffers,
   wetlands or wildlife habitat areas. The remaining land can be rented to
   an active farmer who will follow a conservation plan prepared by
   Natural Resources Conservation Service (NRCS) so that soil and water
   resources are sustained for future generations. Contact your NRCS
   office or visit our web site at www.va.nrcs.usda.gov. P P Actively
   manage woodlands to provide income from timber sales near or after
   retirement. Managing woodlands can improve wildlife habitat and leasing
   hunting rights can also provide income. Contact: Virginia Department of
   Forestry Phone: 804/977-6555 Website: www.dof.state.va.us; Virginia
   Tech Department of Forestry & Virginia Tech Cooperative Extension
   Phone: 540/231-5481 Websites: www.cnr.vt.edu and www.ext.vt.edu
   Virginia Department of Game and Inland Fisheries Phone: 804/387-1000
   Website: www.dgif.state.va.us Virginia Forestry Association Phone:
   804/741-0836 Website: www.vaforestry.org P P Consider a partial or
   whole farm conservation easement : Protect your farm for future
   generations from development and other pressures while realizing
   possible tax benefits. Payment incentives are available for Riparian
   Easements. Contact the Virginia Outdoors Foundation at 540/951-2822 or
   540/886-2460 or visit their website:
   www.virginiaoutdoorsfoundation.org. P P Prepare for estate planning and
   transition : contact your local Virginia Cooperative Extension Office
   or the Virginia Farm Bureau - website www.vafb.com about the Virginia
   Agricultural Vitality Program and Virginia Farm Link or the American
   Farmland Trust - 540/829-5220 or e-mail meheinricht@farmland.org or
